To predict the **sum** and **average** of the stock prices of the **top 5 companies by market cap in 2035**, weâ€™ll build a projection based on:

---

## ğŸ” **1. Historical Trends: Data Summary (2015â€“2024)**

| Year | Sum (Top 5 of 2015) | Avg     | Sum (Top 5 of 2025) | Avg       |
| ---- | ------------------- | ------- | ------------------- | --------- |
| 2015 | \~\$813             | \~\$163 | \~\$1,385           | \~\$277   |
| 2020 | \~\$719             | \~\$144 | \~\$5,058           | \~\$1,012 |
| 2024 | \~\$1,422           | \~\$285 | \~\$6,498           | \~\$1,300 |

* From **2015 to 2024**, the **sum of the 2025-top-5 stock prices** increased nearly **5Ã—**.
* The **2015-top-5 group** rose only **\~75%** in sum during the same period.

So, companies like **NVIDIA, Amazon, Alphabet, Apple, Microsoft** outperformed legacy giants like **Berkshire Hathaway and Exxon** by a wide margin.

---

## ğŸ§  **2. Key Assumptions for 2035 Projection**

1. **Tech dominance continues**, though some shuffling among the top 5 is expected.
2. We assume the top 5 in 2035 will be drawn mostly from today's top 10, possibly with newcomers like **Tesla, Meta, Broadcom, or emerging AI/biotech giants**.
3. We expect **average stock price growth of \~9%â€“12% CAGR** based on historical performance and tech trends.
4. Stock splits and macro events may dampen direct price comparisons but weâ€™ll use adjusted growth for consistency.

---

## ğŸ“ˆ **3. CAGR Estimation (Top 5 of 2025)**

From 2015 â†’ 2024 (9 years), sum grew from \~\$1,385 to \~\$6,498

$$
\text{CAGR} = \left(\frac{6498}{1385}\right)^{1/9} - 1 \approx 18.5\%
$$

Weâ€™ll use **a conservative 12% CAGR** for the next 11 years (2024â€“2035) for the **sum** of stock prices.

---

## ğŸ”® **4. 2035 Projection for 2025 Top 5 Stocks**

$$
\text{Projected Sum}_{2035} = 6498 \times (1.12)^{11} \approx 6498 \times 3.47 \approx \mathbf{\$22,549}
$$

$$
\text{Projected Average}_{2035} = \frac{22,549}{5} \approx \mathbf{\$4,510}
$$

